        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 5:11PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles northeast of Philippi to 10 miles
southeast of Elkins. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Montrose, Harman, Pheasant Run, Bowden, Kerens, Dryfork, Glady, and
Nestorville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Charleston West Virginia.</instruction>
